# Git workflow (agents)

## After every substantive edit session

1. **`git add`** relevant files (not secrets, not `log/`, not `.DS_Store`)
2. **`git commit`** with a clear message (HEREDOC)
3. **`git push origin HEAD`** so Vercel deploys sfjc.dev

Use one step when convenient: `git acp -m "message"` if the repo alias exists; otherwise add → commit → push.

## When to skip commit

- User explicitly says **do not commit** / review only / ask mode
- No file changes
- Only exploratory read-only work

## Do not

- Force-push `main`
- Commit `.env`, credentials, or `log/usage.log`
- Amend pushed commits unless user requests and rules allow

## Also update when relevant

- README changelog for significant changes
- Feature agent docs (e.g. `docs/NOTES-AGENT.md`) when commands/paths change
